The '''1983 Monte Carlo Open''' (also known as the '''Jacomo Monte Carlo Open''' for sponsorship reasons) was a men's [[tennis]] tournament played on [[Clay court|outdoor clay courts]] at the [[Monte Carlo Country Club]] in [[Monte Carlo]], [[Monaco]] that was part of the [[1983 Volvo Grand Prix]]. The tournament was held from 28 March through 1 April 1983.

==Champions==

===Singles===
{{main|1983 Monte Carlo Open – Singles}}
{{flagicon|SWE}} '''[[Mats Wilander]]''' defeated {{flagicon|USA}} [[Mel Purcell]], 6–1, 6–2, 6–3

===Doubles===
{{main|1983 Monte Carlo Open – Doubles}}
{{flagicon|SWI}} '''[[Heinz Günthardt]]''' / {{flagicon|HUN}} '''[[Balázs Taróczy]]''' defeated {{flagicon|FRA}} [[Henri Leconte]] / {{flagicon|FRA}} [[Yannick Noah]], 6–2, 6–4

