{{Infobox military conflict | conflict = Battle of Cerro Muriano | image = Monument a la casa on va nàixer Federico Borrell Garcia, Taino, a Benilloba.JPG | caption = Monument to the "Falling Soldier" Federico Borrell Garcia "Taino" in his home town [[Benilloba]] | partof = the [[Córdoba offensive]], [[Spanish Civil War]] | date = 5–6 September 1936 | place = Cerro Muriano, [[Spain]] | result = Nationalist victory | combatant1 = {{flagicon|Spain|1931}} [[Spanish Republic]] | combatant2 = {{flagicon|Nationalist Spain|1936}} [[Nationalist faction (Spanish Civil War)|Nationalist Spain]] | commander1 = [[José Miaja]] | commander2 = [[José Enrique Varela]] | strength1 = | strength2 = | casualties1 = High | casualties2 = Minimal | campaignbox ={{Campaignbox Spanish Civil War}}}} The '''Battle of Cerro Muriano''' took place during the [[Spanish Civil War]] in 1936.
==Location== Cerro Muriano is a village currently within the municipal terms of [[Córdoba, Andalusia|Córdoba]] and [[Obejo]] in the [[Province of Córdoba (Spain)|Province of Córdoba]].
==History== The battle followed the August [[Córdoba offensive]] and lasted two days, 5 and 6 September 1936. After a 36-hour siege the ''[[Regulares]]'' and the [[Spanish Legion]] troops overran the Republican positions of the ''Columna Miaja'' leaving many dead.<ref>[http://www.photographers.it/articoli/cerro_muriano.htm La battaglia di Cerro Muriano]</ref>
The battle is famous owing to the picture of a [[The Falling Soldier|"falling militiaman"]] taken by [[Robert Capa]], a picture that sought to represent the tragic fate of the Spanish Republic.<ref>[http://www.laguerracivilencordoba.es/art_combatecerromuriano.htm El combate de Cerro Muriano y la foto de robert capa]</ref><ref>[http://www.culturandalucia.com/GCE/Taino/La_identidad_de_Federico_Antonio_Borrell_Garc%C3%ADa_Taino.htm La identidad de "Taino" en una foto atribuida a Robert Capa]</ref>
==See also== *[[The Falling Soldier]] controversy
