{{Infobox diocese |jurisdiction = Diocese |name = Fenoarivo Atsinanana |latin = Dioecesis Fenoarivensis-Atsinananensis |country = {{flag|Madagascar}} |metropolitan = Toamasina |rite = [[Latin Rite]] |cathedral = |cocathedral = |area_km2 = 25,000 |population = 739,116 |population_as_of = 2004 |catholics = 110,850 |catholics_percent= 15.0 |pope = {{Incumbent pope}} |bishop = Marcellin Randriamamonjy }}
The '''Roman Catholic Diocese of Fenoarivo Atsinanana''' ({{lang-la|Fenoariven(sis) – Atsinananen(sis)}}) is a [[diocese]] located in the city of [[Fenoarivo Atsinanana]] in the [[Ecclesiastical province]] of Toamasina in [[Madagascar]].
Its [[cathedral]] episcopal see is the Cathédrale Saint Maurice, in the city of Fenoarivo Atsinanana, Toamasina Province.
==History== * October 30, 2000: Established as Diocese of Fenoarivo Atsinanana from the Metropolitan Archdiocese of Antsiranana
